2313/// When a match is complete, this method updates uses of interior chain results
2314/// to use the new results.
2315void SelectionDAGISel::UpdateChains(
2316 SDNode *NodeToMatch, SDValue InputChain,
2317 SmallVectorImpl<SDNode *> &ChainNodesMatched, bool isMorphNodeTo) {
2318 SmallVector<SDNode*, 4> NowDeadNodes;
2319
2320 // Now that all the normal results are replaced, we replace the chain and
2321 // glue results if present.
2322 if (!ChainNodesMatched.empty()) {
2323 assert(InputChain.getNode() &&
2324 "Matched input chains but didn't produce a chain");
2325 // Loop over all of the nodes we matched that produced a chain result.
2326 // Replace all the chain results with the final chain we ended up with.
2327 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ChainNodesMatched.size(); i != e; ++i) {
2328 SDNode *ChainNode = ChainNodesMatched[i];
2329 // If ChainNode is null, it's because we replaced it on a previous
2330 // iteration and we cleared it out of the map. Just skip it.
2331 if (!ChainNode)
2332 continue;
2333
2334 assert(ChainNode->getOpcode() != ISD::DELETED_NODE &&
2335 "Deleted node left in chain");
2336
2337 // Don't replace the results of the root node if we're doing a
2338 // MorphNodeTo.
2339 if (ChainNode == NodeToMatch && isMorphNodeTo)
2340 continue;
2341
2342 SDValue ChainVal = SDValue(ChainNode, ChainNode->getNumValues()-1);
2343 if (ChainVal.getValueType() == MVT::Glue)
2344 ChainVal = ChainVal.getValue(ChainVal->getNumValues()-2);
2345 assert(ChainVal.getValueType() == MVT::Other && "Not a chain?");
2346 SelectionDAG::DAGNodeDeletedListener NDL(
2347 *CurDAG, [&](SDNode *N, SDNode *E) {
2348 std::replace(ChainNodesMatched.begin(), ChainNodesMatched.end(), N,
2349 static_cast<SDNode *>(nullptr));
2350 });
2351 if (ChainNode->getOpcode() != ISD::TokenFactor)
2352 ReplaceUses(ChainVal, InputChain);
2353
2354 // If the node became dead and we haven't already seen it, delete it.
2355 if (ChainNode != NodeToMatch && ChainNode->use_empty() &&
2356 !llvm::is_contained(NowDeadNodes, ChainNode))
2357 NowDeadNodes.push_back(ChainNode);
2358 }
2359 }
2360
2361 if (!NowDeadNodes.empty())
2362 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNodes(NowDeadNodes);
2363
2364 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ISEL: Match complete!\n");
2365}
2366
2367/// HandleMergeInputChains - This implements the OPC_EmitMergeInputChains
2368/// operation for when the pattern matched at least one node with a chains. The
2369/// input vector contains a list of all of the chained nodes that we match. We
2370/// must determine if this is a valid thing to cover (i.e. matching it won't
2371/// induce cycles in the DAG) and if so, creating a TokenFactor node. that will
2372/// be used as the input node chain for the generated nodes.
2373static SDValue
2374HandleMergeInputChains(SmallVectorImpl<SDNode*> &ChainNodesMatched,
2375 SelectionDAG *CurDAG) {
2376
2377 SmallPtrSet<const SDNode *, 16> Visited;
2378 SmallVector<const SDNode *, 8> Worklist;
2379 SmallVector<SDValue, 3> InputChains;
2380 unsigned int Max = 8192;
2381
2382 // Quick exit on trivial merge.
2383 if (ChainNodesMatched.size() == 1)
2384 return ChainNodesMatched[0]->getOperand(0);
2385
2386 // Add chains that aren't already added (internal). Peek through
2387 // token factors.
2388 std::function<void(const SDValue)> AddChains = [&](const SDValue V) {
2389 if (V.getValueType() != MVT::Other)
2390 return;
2391 if (V->getOpcode() == ISD::EntryToken)
2392 return;
2393 if (!Visited.insert(V.getNode()).second)
2394 return;
2395 if (V->getOpcode() == ISD::TokenFactor) {
2396 for (const SDValue &Op : V->op_values())
2397 AddChains(Op);
2398 } else
2399 InputChains.push_back(V);
2400 };
2401
2402 for (auto *N : ChainNodesMatched) {
2403 Worklist.push_back(N);
2404 Visited.insert(N);
2405 }
2406
2407 while (!Worklist.empty())
2408 AddChains(Worklist.pop_back_val()->getOperand(0));
2409
2410 // Skip the search if there are no chain dependencies.
2411 if (InputChains.size() == 0)
2412 return CurDAG->getEntryNode();
2413
2414 // If one of these chains is a successor of input, we must have a
2415 // node that is both the predecessor and successor of the
2416 // to-be-merged nodes. Fail.
2417 Visited.clear();
2418 for (SDValue V : InputChains)
2419 Worklist.push_back(V.getNode());
2420
2421 for (auto *N : ChainNodesMatched)
2422 if (SDNode::hasPredecessorHelper(N, Visited, Worklist, Max, true))
2423 return SDValue();
2424
2425 // Return merged chain.
2426 if (InputChains.size() == 1)
2427 return InputChains[0];
2428 return CurDAG->getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, SDLoc(ChainNodesMatched[0]),
2429 MVT::Other, InputChains);
2430}
2431
2432/// MorphNode - Handle morphing a node in place for the selector.
2433SDNode *SelectionDAGISel::
2434MorphNode(SDNode *Node, unsigned TargetOpc, SDVTList VTList,
2435 ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops, unsigned EmitNodeInfo) {
2436 // It is possible we're using MorphNodeTo to replace a node with no
2437 // normal results with one that has a normal result (or we could be
2438 // adding a chain) and the input could have glue and chains as well.
2439 // In this case we need to shift the operands down.
2440 // FIXME: This is a horrible hack and broken in obscure cases, no worse
2441 // than the old isel though.
2442 int OldGlueResultNo = -1, OldChainResultNo = -1;
2443
2444 unsigned NTMNumResults = Node->getNumValues();
2445 if (Node->getValueType(NTMNumResults-1) == MVT::Glue) {
2446 OldGlueResultNo = NTMNumResults-1;
2447 if (NTMNumResults != 1 &&
2448 Node->getValueType(NTMNumResults-2) == MVT::Other)
2449 OldChainResultNo = NTMNumResults-2;
2450 } else if (Node->getValueType(NTMNumResults-1) == MVT::Other)
2451 OldChainResultNo = NTMNumResults-1;
2452
2453 // Call the underlying SelectionDAG routine to do the transmogrification. Note
2454 // that this deletes operands of the old node that become dead.
2455 SDNode *Res = CurDAG->MorphNodeTo(Node, ~TargetOpc, VTList, Ops);
2456
2457 // MorphNodeTo can operate in two ways: if an existing node with the
2458 // specified operands exists, it can just return it. Otherwise, it
2459 // updates the node in place to have the requested operands.
2460 if (Res == Node) {
2461 // If we updated the node in place, reset the node ID. To the isel,
2462 // this should be just like a newly allocated machine node.
2463 Res->setNodeId(-1);
2464 }
2465
2466 unsigned ResNumResults = Res->getNumValues();
2467 // Move the glue if needed.
2468 if ((EmitNodeInfo & OPFL_GlueOutput) && OldGlueResultNo != -1 &&
2469 (unsigned)OldGlueResultNo != ResNumResults-1)
2470 ReplaceUses(SDValue(Node, OldGlueResultNo),
2471 SDValue(Res, ResNumResults - 1));
2472
2473 if ((EmitNodeInfo & OPFL_GlueOutput) != 0)
2474 --ResNumResults;
2475
2476 // Move the chain reference if needed.
2477 if ((EmitNodeInfo & OPFL_Chain) && OldChainResultNo != -1 &&
2478 (unsigned)OldChainResultNo != ResNumResults-1)
2479 ReplaceUses(SDValue(Node, OldChainResultNo),
2480 SDValue(Res, ResNumResults - 1));
2481
2482 // Otherwise, no replacement happened because the node already exists. Replace
2483 // Uses of the old node with the new one.
2484 if (Res != Node) {
2485 ReplaceNode(Node, Res);
2486 } else {
2487 EnforceNodeIdInvariant(Res);
2488 }
2489
2490 return Res;
2491}

2493/// CheckSame - Implements OP_CheckSame.
2494LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static bool
2495CheckSame(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex, SDValue N,
2496 const SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<SDValue, SDNode *>> &RecordedNodes) {
2497 // Accept if it is exactly the same as a previously recorded node.
2498 unsigned RecNo = MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2499 assert(RecNo < RecordedNodes.size() && "Invalid CheckSame");
2500 return N == RecordedNodes[RecNo].first;
2501}

2503/// CheckChildSame - Implements OP_CheckChildXSame.
2504LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static bool CheckChildSame(
2505 const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex, SDValue N,
2506 const SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<SDValue, SDNode *>> &RecordedNodes,
2507 unsigned ChildNo) {
2508 if (ChildNo >= N.getNumOperands())
2509 return false; // Match fails if out of range child #.
2510 return ::CheckSame(MatcherTable, MatcherIndex, N.getOperand(ChildNo),
2511 RecordedNodes);
2512}

2516CheckPatternPredicate(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex,
2517 const SelectionDAGISel &SDISel) {
2518 return SDISel.CheckPatternPredicate(MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++]);
2519}

2521/// CheckNodePredicate - Implements OP_CheckNodePredicate.

2523CheckNodePredicate(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex,
2524 const SelectionDAGISel &SDISel, SDNode *N) {
2525 return SDISel.CheckNodePredicate(N, MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++]);
2526}

2528LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static bool
2529CheckOpcode(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex,
2530 SDNode *N) {
2531 uint16_t Opc = MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2532 Opc |= (unsigned short)MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++] << 8;
2533 return N->getOpcode() == Opc;
2534}
2535
2536LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static bool
2537CheckType(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex, SDValue N,
2538 const TargetLowering *TLI, const DataLayout &DL) {
2539 MVT::SimpleValueType VT = (MVT::SimpleValueType)MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2540 if (N.getValueType() == VT) return true;
2541
2542 // Handle the case when VT is iPTR.
2543 return VT == MVT::iPTR && N.getValueType() == TLI->getPointerTy(DL);
2544}
2545
2546LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static bool
2547CheckChildType(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex,
2548 SDValue N, const TargetLowering *TLI, const DataLayout &DL,
2549 unsigned ChildNo) {
2550 if (ChildNo >= N.getNumOperands())
2551 return false; // Match fails if out of range child #.
2552 return ::CheckType(MatcherTable, MatcherIndex, N.getOperand(ChildNo), TLI,
2553 DL);
2554}

2556LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static bool
2557CheckCondCode(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex,
2558 SDValue N) {
2559 return cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N)->get() ==
2560 (ISD::CondCode)MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2561}
2562
2563LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static bool
2564CheckChild2CondCode(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex,
2565 SDValue N) {
2566 if (2 >= N.getNumOperands())
2567 return false;
2568 return ::CheckCondCode(MatcherTable, MatcherIndex, N.getOperand(2));
2569}
2570
2571LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static bool
2572CheckValueType(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex,
2573 SDValue N, const TargetLowering *TLI, const DataLayout &DL) {
2574 MVT::SimpleValueType VT = (MVT::SimpleValueType)MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2575 if (cast<VTSDNode>(N)->getVT() == VT)
2576 return true;
2577
2578 // Handle the case when VT is iPTR.
2579 return VT == MVT::iPTR && cast<VTSDNode>(N)->getVT() == TLI->getPointerTy(DL);
2580}
2581
2582LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static bool
2583CheckInteger(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex,
2584 SDValue N) {
2585 int64_t Val = MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2586 if (Val & 128)
2587 Val = GetVBR(Val, MatcherTable, MatcherIndex);
2588
2589 ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N);
2590 return C && C->getSExtValue() == Val;
2591}
2592
2593LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static bool
2594CheckChildInteger(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex,
2595 SDValue N, unsigned ChildNo) {
2596 if (ChildNo >= N.getNumOperands())
2597 return false; // Match fails if out of range child #.
2598 return ::CheckInteger(MatcherTable, MatcherIndex, N.getOperand(ChildNo));
2599}
2600
2601LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static bool
2602CheckAndImm(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex,
2603 SDValue N, const SelectionDAGISel &SDISel) {
2604 int64_t Val = MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2605 if (Val & 128)
2606 Val = GetVBR(Val, MatcherTable, MatcherIndex);
2607
2608 if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::AND) return false;
2609
2610 ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
2611 return C && SDISel.CheckAndMask(N.getOperand(0), C, Val);
2612}
2613
2614LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static bool
2615CheckOrImm(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex, SDValue N,
2616 const SelectionDAGISel &SDISel) {
2617 int64_t Val = MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2618 if (Val & 128)
2619 Val = GetVBR(Val, MatcherTable, MatcherIndex);
2620
2621 if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::OR) return false;
2622
2623 ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
2624 return C && SDISel.CheckOrMask(N.getOperand(0), C, Val);
2625}
2626
2627/// IsPredicateKnownToFail - If we know how and can do so without pushing a
2628/// scope, evaluate the current node. If the current predicate is known to
2629/// fail, set Result=true and return anything. If the current predicate is
2630/// known to pass, set Result=false and return the MatcherIndex to continue
2631/// with. If the current predicate is unknown, set Result=false and return the
2632/// MatcherIndex to continue with.
2633static unsigned IsPredicateKnownToFail(const unsigned char *Table,
2634 unsigned Index, SDValue N,
2635 bool &Result,
2636 const SelectionDAGISel &SDISel,
2637 SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<SDValue, SDNode*>> &RecordedNodes) {
2638 switch (Table[Index++]) {
2639 default:
2640 Result = false;
2641 return Index-1; // Could not evaluate this predicate.
2642 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckSame:
2643 Result = !::CheckSame(Table, Index, N, RecordedNodes);
2644 return Index;
2645 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild0Same:
2646 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild1Same:
2647 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild2Same:
2648 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild3Same:
2649 Result = !::CheckChildSame(Table, Index, N, RecordedNodes,
2650 Table[Index-1] - SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild0Same);
2651 return Index;
2652 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckPatternPredicate:
2653 Result = !::CheckPatternPredicate(Table, Index, SDISel);
2654 return Index;
2655 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckPredicate:
2656 Result = !::CheckNodePredicate(Table, Index, SDISel, N.getNode());
2657 return Index;
2658 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckOpcode:
2659 Result = !::CheckOpcode(Table, Index, N.getNode());
2660 return Index;
2661 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckType:
2662 Result = !::CheckType(Table, Index, N, SDISel.TLI,
2663 SDISel.CurDAG->getDataLayout());
2664 return Index;
2665 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckTypeRes: {
2666 unsigned Res = Table[Index++];
2667 Result = !::CheckType(Table, Index, N.getValue(Res), SDISel.TLI,
2668 SDISel.CurDAG->getDataLayout());
2669 return Index;
2670 }
2671 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild0Type:
2672 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild1Type:
2673 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild2Type:
2674 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild3Type:
2675 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild4Type:
2676 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild5Type:
2677 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild6Type:
2678 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild7Type:
2679 Result = !::CheckChildType(
2680 Table, Index, N, SDISel.TLI, SDISel.CurDAG->getDataLayout(),
2681 Table[Index - 1] - SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild0Type);
2682 return Index;
2683 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckCondCode:
2684 Result = !::CheckCondCode(Table, Index, N);
2685 return Index;
2686 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild2CondCode:
2687 Result = !::CheckChild2CondCode(Table, Index, N);
2688 return Index;
2689 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckValueType:
2690 Result = !::CheckValueType(Table, Index, N, SDISel.TLI,
2691 SDISel.CurDAG->getDataLayout());
2692 return Index;
2693 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckInteger:
2694 Result = !::CheckInteger(Table, Index, N);
2695 return Index;
2696 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild0Integer:
2697 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild1Integer:
2698 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild2Integer:
2699 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild3Integer:
2700 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild4Integer:
2701 Result = !::CheckChildInteger(Table, Index, N,
2702 Table[Index-1] - SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild0Integer);
2703 return Index;
2704 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckAndImm:
2705 Result = !::CheckAndImm(Table, Index, N, SDISel);
2706 return Index;
2707 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckOrImm:
2708 Result = !::CheckOrImm(Table, Index, N, SDISel);
2709 return Index;
2710 }
2711}

2713namespace {
2714
2715struct MatchScope {
2716 /// FailIndex - If this match fails, this is the index to continue with.
2717 unsigned FailIndex;
2718
2719 /// NodeStack - The node stack when the scope was formed.
2720 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> NodeStack;
2721
2722 /// NumRecordedNodes - The number of recorded nodes when the scope was formed.
2723 unsigned NumRecordedNodes;
2724
2725 /// NumMatchedMemRefs - The number of matched memref entries.
2726 unsigned NumMatchedMemRefs;
2727
2728 /// InputChain/InputGlue - The current chain/glue
2729 SDValue InputChain, InputGlue;
2730
2731 /// HasChainNodesMatched - True if the ChainNodesMatched list is non-empty.
2732 bool HasChainNodesMatched;
2733};
2734
2735/// \A DAG update listener to keep the matching state
2736/// (i.e. RecordedNodes and MatchScope) uptodate if the target is allowed to
2737/// change the DAG while matching. X86 addressing mode matcher is an example
2738/// for this.
2739class MatchStateUpdater : public SelectionDAG::DAGUpdateListener
2740{
2741 SDNode **NodeToMatch;
2742 SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<SDValue, SDNode *>> &RecordedNodes;
2743 SmallVectorImpl<MatchScope> &MatchScopes;
2744
2745public:
2746 MatchStateUpdater(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDNode **NodeToMatch,
2747 SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<SDValue, SDNode *>> &RN,
2748 SmallVectorImpl<MatchScope> &MS)
2749 : SelectionDAG::DAGUpdateListener(DAG), NodeToMatch(NodeToMatch),
2750 RecordedNodes(RN), MatchScopes(MS) {}
2751
2752 void NodeDeleted(SDNode *N, SDNode *E) override {
2753 // Some early-returns here to avoid the search if we deleted the node or
2754 // if the update comes from MorphNodeTo (MorphNodeTo is the last thing we
2755 // do, so it's unnecessary to update matching state at that point).
2756 // Neither of these can occur currently because we only install this
2757 // update listener during matching a complex patterns.
2758 if (!E || E->isMachineOpcode())
2759 return;
2760 // Check if NodeToMatch was updated.
2761 if (N == *NodeToMatch)
2762 *NodeToMatch = E;
2763 // Performing linear search here does not matter because we almost never
2764 // run this code. You'd have to have a CSE during complex pattern
2765 // matching.
2766 for (auto &I : RecordedNodes)
2767 if (I.first.getNode() == N)
2768 I.first.setNode(E);
2769
2770 for (auto &I : MatchScopes)
2771 for (auto &J : I.NodeStack)
2772 if (J.getNode() == N)
2773 J.setNode(E);
2774 }
2775};
2776
2777} // end anonymous namespace
2778
2779void SelectionDAGISel::SelectCodeCommon(SDNode *NodeToMatch,
2780 const unsigned char *MatcherTable,
2781 unsigned TableSize) {
2782 // FIXME: Should these even be selected? Handle these cases in the caller?
2783 switch (NodeToMatch->getOpcode()) {
2784 default:
2785 break;
2786 case ISD::EntryToken: // These nodes remain the same.
2787 case ISD::BasicBlock:
2788 case ISD::Register:
2789 case ISD::RegisterMask:
2790 case ISD::HANDLENODE:
2791 case ISD::MDNODE_SDNODE:
2792 case ISD::TargetConstant:
2793 case ISD::TargetConstantFP:
2794 case ISD::TargetConstantPool:
2795 case ISD::TargetFrameIndex:
2796 case ISD::TargetExternalSymbol:
2797 case ISD::MCSymbol:
2798 case ISD::TargetBlockAddress:
2799 case ISD::TargetJumpTable:
2800 case ISD::TargetGlobalTLSAddress:
2801 case ISD::TargetGlobalAddress:
2802 case ISD::TokenFactor:
2803 case ISD::CopyFromReg:
2804 case ISD::CopyToReg:
2805 case ISD::EH_LABEL:
2806 case ISD::ANNOTATION_LABEL:
2807 case ISD::LIFETIME_START:
2808 case ISD::LIFETIME_END:
2809 case ISD::PSEUDO_PROBE:
2810 NodeToMatch->setNodeId(-1); // Mark selected.
2811 return;
2812 case ISD::AssertSext:
2813 case ISD::AssertZext:
2814 case ISD::AssertAlign:
2815 ReplaceUses(SDValue(NodeToMatch, 0), NodeToMatch->getOperand(0));
2816 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(NodeToMatch);
2817 return;
2818 case ISD::INLINEASM:
2819 case ISD::INLINEASM_BR:
2820 Select_INLINEASM(NodeToMatch);
2821 return;
2822 case ISD::READ_REGISTER:
2823 Select_READ_REGISTER(NodeToMatch);
2824 return;
2825 case ISD::WRITE_REGISTER:
2826 Select_WRITE_REGISTER(NodeToMatch);
2827 return;
2828 case ISD::UNDEF:
2829 Select_UNDEF(NodeToMatch);
2830 return;
2831 case ISD::FREEZE:
2832 Select_FREEZE(NodeToMatch);
2833 return;
2834 }
2835
2836 assert(!NodeToMatch->isMachineOpcode() && "Node already selected!");
2837
2838 // Set up the node stack with NodeToMatch as the only node on the stack.
2839 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> NodeStack;
2840 SDValue N = SDValue(NodeToMatch, 0);
2841 NodeStack.push_back(N);
2842
2843 // MatchScopes - Scopes used when matching, if a match failure happens, this
2844 // indicates where to continue checking.
2845 SmallVector<MatchScope, 8> MatchScopes;
2846
2847 // RecordedNodes - This is the set of nodes that have been recorded by the
2848 // state machine. The second value is the parent of the node, or null if the
2849 // root is recorded.
2850 SmallVector<std::pair<SDValue, SDNode*>, 8> RecordedNodes;
2851
2852 // MatchedMemRefs - This is the set of MemRef's we've seen in the input
2853 // pattern.
2854 SmallVector<MachineMemOperand*, 2> MatchedMemRefs;
2855
2856 // These are the current input chain and glue for use when generating nodes.
2857 // Various Emit operations change these. For example, emitting a copytoreg
2858 // uses and updates these.
2859 SDValue InputChain, InputGlue;
2860
2861 // ChainNodesMatched - If a pattern matches nodes that have input/output
2862 // chains, the OPC_EmitMergeInputChains operation is emitted which indicates
2863 // which ones they are. The result is captured into this list so that we can
2864 // update the chain results when the pattern is complete.
2865 SmallVector<SDNode*, 3> ChainNodesMatched;
2866
2867 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ISEL: Starting pattern match\n");
2868
2869 // Determine where to start the interpreter. Normally we start at opcode #0,
2870 // but if the state machine starts with an OPC_SwitchOpcode, then we
2871 // accelerate the first lookup (which is guaranteed to be hot) with the
2872 // OpcodeOffset table.
2873 unsigned MatcherIndex = 0;
2874
2875 if (!OpcodeOffset.empty()) {
2876 // Already computed the OpcodeOffset table, just index into it.
2877 if (N.getOpcode() < OpcodeOffset.size())
2878 MatcherIndex = OpcodeOffset[N.getOpcode()];
2879 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Initial Opcode index to " << MatcherIndex << "\n");
2880
2881 } else if (MatcherTable[0] == OPC_SwitchOpcode) {
2882 // Otherwise, the table isn't computed, but the state machine does start
2883 // with an OPC_SwitchOpcode instruction. Populate the table now, since this
2884 // is the first time we're selecting an instruction.
2885 unsigned Idx = 1;
2886 while (true) {
2887 // Get the size of this case.
2888 unsigned CaseSize = MatcherTable[Idx++];
2889 if (CaseSize & 128)
2890 CaseSize = GetVBR(CaseSize, MatcherTable, Idx);
2891 if (CaseSize == 0) break;
2892
2893 // Get the opcode, add the index to the table.
2894 uint16_t Opc = MatcherTable[Idx++];
2895 Opc |= (unsigned short)MatcherTable[Idx++] << 8;
2896 if (Opc >= OpcodeOffset.size())
2897 OpcodeOffset.resize((Opc+1)*2);
2898 OpcodeOffset[Opc] = Idx;
2899 Idx += CaseSize;
2900 }
2901
2902 // Okay, do the lookup for the first opcode.
2903 if (N.getOpcode() < OpcodeOffset.size())
2904 MatcherIndex = OpcodeOffset[N.getOpcode()];
2905 }
2906
2907 while (true) {
2908 assert(MatcherIndex < TableSize && "Invalid index");
2909#ifndef NDEBUG
2910 unsigned CurrentOpcodeIndex = MatcherIndex;
2911#endif
2912 BuiltinOpcodes Opcode = (BuiltinOpcodes)MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2913 switch (Opcode) {
2914 case OPC_Scope: {
2915 // Okay, the semantics of this operation are that we should push a scope
2916 // then evaluate the first child. However, pushing a scope only to have
2917 // the first check fail (which then pops it) is inefficient. If we can
2918 // determine immediately that the first check (or first several) will
2919 // immediately fail, don't even bother pushing a scope for them.
2920 unsigned FailIndex;
2921
2922 while (true) {
2923 unsigned NumToSkip = MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2924 if (NumToSkip & 128)
2925 NumToSkip = GetVBR(NumToSkip, MatcherTable, MatcherIndex);
2926 // Found the end of the scope with no match.
2927 if (NumToSkip == 0) {
2928 FailIndex = 0;
2929 break;
2930 }
2931
2932 FailIndex = MatcherIndex+NumToSkip;
2933
2934 unsigned MatcherIndexOfPredicate = MatcherIndex;
2935 (void)MatcherIndexOfPredicate; // silence warning.
2936
2937 // If we can't evaluate this predicate without pushing a scope (e.g. if
2938 // it is a 'MoveParent') or if the predicate succeeds on this node, we
2939 // push the scope and evaluate the full predicate chain.
2940 bool Result;
2941 MatcherIndex = IsPredicateKnownToFail(MatcherTable, MatcherIndex, N,
2942 Result, *this, RecordedNodes);
2943 if (!Result)
2944 break;
2945
2946 LLVM_DEBUG(
2947 dbgs() << " Skipped scope entry (due to false predicate) at "
2948 << "index " << MatcherIndexOfPredicate << ", continuing at "
2949 << FailIndex << "\n");
2950 ++NumDAGIselRetries;
2951
2952 // Otherwise, we know that this case of the Scope is guaranteed to fail,
2953 // move to the next case.
2954 MatcherIndex = FailIndex;
2955 }
2956
2957 // If the whole scope failed to match, bail.
2958 if (FailIndex == 0) break;
2959
2960 // Push a MatchScope which indicates where to go if the first child fails
2961 // to match.
2962 MatchScope NewEntry;
2963 NewEntry.FailIndex = FailIndex;
2964 NewEntry.NodeStack.append(NodeStack.begin(), NodeStack.end());
2965 NewEntry.NumRecordedNodes = RecordedNodes.size();
2966 NewEntry.NumMatchedMemRefs = MatchedMemRefs.size();
2967 NewEntry.InputChain = InputChain;
2968 NewEntry.InputGlue = InputGlue;
2969 NewEntry.HasChainNodesMatched = !ChainNodesMatched.empty();
2970 MatchScopes.push_back(NewEntry);
2971 continue;
2972 }
2973 case OPC_RecordNode: {
2974 // Remember this node, it may end up being an operand in the pattern.
2975 SDNode *Parent = nullptr;
2976 if (NodeStack.size() > 1)
2977 Parent = NodeStack[NodeStack.size()-2].getNode();
2978 RecordedNodes.push_back(std::make_pair(N, Parent));
2979 continue;
2980 }
2981
2982 case OPC_RecordChild0: case OPC_RecordChild1:
2983 case OPC_RecordChild2: case OPC_RecordChild3:
2984 case OPC_RecordChild4: case OPC_RecordChild5:
2985 case OPC_RecordChild6: case OPC_RecordChild7: {
2986 unsigned ChildNo = Opcode-OPC_RecordChild0;

3526 Res->setFlags(Flags);

3530 // chain and glue.
3531 if (EmitNodeInfo & OPFL_GlueOutput) {
3532 InputGlue = SDValue(Res, VTs.size()-1);
3533 if (EmitNodeInfo & OPFL_Chain)
3534 InputChain = SDValue(Res, VTs.size()-2);
3535 } else if (EmitNodeInfo & OPFL_Chain)
3536 InputChain = SDValue(Res, VTs.size()-1);
3537
3538 // If the OPFL_MemRefs glue is set on this node, slap all of the

3543 // loads.
3544 if (EmitNodeInfo & OPFL_MemRefs) {

3546 // instruction may load or store.

3548 bool mayLoad = MCID.mayLoad();
3549 bool mayStore = MCID.mayStore();
3550
3551 // We expect to have relatively few of these so just filter them into a
3552 // temporary buffer so that we can easily add them to the instruction.
3553 SmallVector<MachineMemOperand *, 4> FilteredMemRefs;
3554 for (MachineMemOperand *MMO : MatchedMemRefs) {
3555 if (MMO->isLoad()) {
3556 if (mayLoad)
3557 FilteredMemRefs.push_back(MMO);
3558 } else if (MMO->isStore()) {
3559 if (mayStore)
3560 FilteredMemRefs.push_back(MMO);
3561 } else {
3562 FilteredMemRefs.push_back(MMO);
3563 }
3564 }
3565
3566 CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(Res, FilteredMemRefs);
3567 }

3569 LLVM_DEBUG(if (!MatchedMemRefs.empty() && Res->memoperands_empty()) dbgs()

3572 << " node: ";

3574
3575 // If this was a MorphNodeTo then we're completely done!
3576 if (IsMorphNodeTo) {
3577 // Update chain uses.
3578 UpdateChains(Res, InputChain, ChainNodesMatched, true);
3579 return;
3580 }
3581 continue;
3582 }
3583
3584 case OPC_CompleteMatch: {
3585 // The match has been completed, and any new nodes (if any) have been
3586 // created. Patch up references to the matched dag to use the newly
3587 // created nodes.
3588 unsigned NumResults = MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
3589
3590 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumResults; ++i) {
3591 unsigned ResSlot = MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
3592 if (ResSlot & 128)
3593 ResSlot = GetVBR(ResSlot, MatcherTable, MatcherIndex);
3594
3595 assert(ResSlot < RecordedNodes.size() && "Invalid CompleteMatch");
3596 SDValue Res = RecordedNodes[ResSlot].first;
3597
3598 assert(i < NodeToMatch->getNumValues() &&
3599 NodeToMatch->getValueType(i) != MVT::Other &&
3600 NodeToMatch->getValueType(i) != MVT::Glue &&
3601 "Invalid number of results to complete!");
3602 assert((NodeToMatch->getValueType(i) == Res.getValueType() ||
3603 NodeToMatch->getValueType(i) == MVT::iPTR ||
3604 Res.getValueType() == MVT::iPTR ||
3605 NodeToMatch->getValueType(i).getSizeInBits() ==
3606 Res.getValueSizeInBits()) &&
3607 "invalid replacement");
3608 ReplaceUses(SDValue(NodeToMatch, i), Res);
3609 }
3610
3611 // Update chain uses.
3612 UpdateChains(NodeToMatch, InputChain, ChainNodesMatched, false);
3613
3614 // If the root node defines glue, we need to update it to the glue result.
3615 // TODO: This never happens in our tests and I think it can be removed /
3616 // replaced with an assert, but if we do it this the way the change is
3617 // NFC.
3618 if (NodeToMatch->getValueType(NodeToMatch->getNumValues() - 1) ==
3619 MVT::Glue &&
3620 InputGlue.getNode())
3621 ReplaceUses(SDValue(NodeToMatch, NodeToMatch->getNumValues() - 1),
3622 InputGlue);
3623
3624 assert(NodeToMatch->use_empty() &&
3625 "Didn't replace all uses of the node?");
3626 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(NodeToMatch);
3627
3628 return;
3629 }
3630 }
3631
3632 // If the code reached this point, then the match failed. See if there is
3633 // another child to try in the current 'Scope', otherwise pop it until we
3634 // find a case to check.
3635 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Match failed at index " << CurrentOpcodeIndex
3636 << "\n");
3637 ++NumDAGIselRetries;
3638 while (true) {
3639 if (MatchScopes.empty()) {
3640 CannotYetSelect(NodeToMatch);
3641 return;
3642 }
3643
3644 // Restore the interpreter state back to the point where the scope was
3645 // formed.
3646 MatchScope &LastScope = MatchScopes.back();
3647 RecordedNodes.resize(LastScope.NumRecordedNodes);
3648 NodeStack.clear();
3649 NodeStack.append(LastScope.NodeStack.begin(), LastScope.NodeStack.end());
3650 N = NodeStack.back();
3651
3652 if (LastScope.NumMatchedMemRefs != MatchedMemRefs.size())
3653 MatchedMemRefs.resize(LastScope.NumMatchedMemRefs);
3654 MatcherIndex = LastScope.FailIndex;
3655
3656 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Continuing at " << MatcherIndex << "\n");
3657
3658 InputChain = LastScope.InputChain;
3659 InputGlue = LastScope.InputGlue;
3660 if (!LastScope.HasChainNodesMatched)
3661 ChainNodesMatched.clear();
3662
3663 // Check to see what the offset is at the new MatcherIndex. If it is zero
3664 // we have reached the end of this scope, otherwise we have another child
3665 // in the current scope to try.
3666 unsigned NumToSkip = MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
3667 if (NumToSkip & 128)
3668 NumToSkip = GetVBR(NumToSkip, MatcherTable, MatcherIndex);
3669
3670 // If we have another child in this scope to match, update FailIndex and
3671 // try it.
3672 if (NumToSkip != 0) {
3673 LastScope.FailIndex = MatcherIndex+NumToSkip;
3674 break;
3675 }
3676
3677 // End of this scope, pop it and try the next child in the containing
3678 // scope.
3679 MatchScopes.pop_back();
3680 }
3681 }
3682}

3684/// Return whether the node may raise an FP exception.
3685bool SelectionDAGISel::mayRaiseFPException(SDNode *N) const {
3686 // For machine opcodes, consult the MCID flag.
3687 if (N->isMachineOpcode()) {
3688 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = TII->get(N->getMachineOpcode());
3689 return MCID.mayRaiseFPException();
3690 }
3691
3692 // For ISD opcodes, only StrictFP opcodes may raise an FP
3693 // exception.
3694 if (N->isTargetOpcode())
3695 return N->isTargetStrictFPOpcode();
3696 return N->isStrictFPOpcode();
3697}

3699bool SelectionDAGISel::isOrEquivalentToAdd(const SDNode *N) const {
3700 assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::OR && "Unexpected opcode");
3701 auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
3702 if (!C)
3703 return false;
3704
3705 // Detect when "or" is used to add an offset to a stack object.
3706 if (auto *FN = dyn_cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(N->getOperand(0))) {
3707 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF->getFrameInfo();
3708 Align A = MFI.getObjectAlign(FN->getIndex());
3709 int32_t Off = C->getSExtValue();
3710 // If the alleged offset fits in the zero bits guaranteed by
3711 // the alignment, then this or is really an add.
3712 return (Off >= 0) && (((A.value() - 1) & Off) == unsigned(Off));
3713 }
3714 return false;
3715}

3717void SelectionDAGISel::CannotYetSelect(SDNode *N) {
3718 std::string msg;
3719 raw_string_ostream Msg(msg);
3720 Msg << "Cannot select: ";
3721
3722 if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN &&
3723 N->getOpcode() != ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN &&
3724 N->getOpcode() != ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID) {
3725 N->printrFull(Msg, CurDAG);
3726 Msg << "\nIn function: " << MF->getName();
3727 } else {
3728 bool HasInputChain = N->getOperand(0).getValueType() == MVT::Other;
3729 unsigned iid =
3730 cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(HasInputChain))->getZExtValue();
3731 if (iid < Intrinsic::num_intrinsics)
3732 Msg << "intrinsic %" << Intrinsic::getName((Intrinsic::ID)iid, None);
3733 else if (const TargetIntrinsicInfo *TII = TM.getIntrinsicInfo())
3734 Msg << "target intrinsic %" << TII->getName(iid);
3735 else
3736 Msg << "unknown intrinsic #" << iid;
3737 }
3738 report_fatal_error(Msg.str());
3739}
